<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,1483,1618]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spiridonov, Neretina &amp; Schepetov" authorityYear="2014" box="[321,452,1483,1509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ovalipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ovalipiinae">Ovalipiinae</taxonomicName>
was described as family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spiridonov, Neretina &amp; Schepetov" authorityYear="2014" box="[735,858,1483,1509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ovalipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ovalipidae</taxonomicName>
by Spirodonov 
<emphasis box="[1038,1094,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2014). However, Spirodonov (2020), in agreement with the suggestion by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, N." box="[674,827,1519,1546]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref44458" refString="Evans, N. (2018) Molecular phylogenetics of swimming crabs (Portunoidea Rafinesque, 1815) supports a revised family-level classification and suggests a single derived origin of symbiotic taxa. PeerJ, 6 (e 4260), 1 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 4260" type="journal article" year="2018">Evans (2018)</bibRefCitation>
based on his molecular phylogenetic reconstruction, accepted the closer relationships of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1898" box="[554,654,1555,1581]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ovalipidae" genus="Ovalipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,654,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Ovalipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with geryonids and consequently moved this group as a subfamily of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colosi" authorityYear="1923" box="[192,323,1591,1617]" class="Malacostraca" family="Geryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geryonidae</taxonomicName>
with only one genus. They are pelagic species known as swimming crabs (
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley, B." box="[1165,1324,1591,1617]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref47372" refString="Kensley, B. (1981) On the zoogeography of southern African Decapod Crustacea, with a distributional checklist of the species. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 338, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1981">Kensley 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
